INSERT INTO public.theory_quiz_bank (course_id, question, reference_answer) VALUES
('203ee6ac-e5c8-4644-bb3c-855884ba8de4', 'How does the Evaluation phase differ from the "assess model" step in the Modeling phase?', 'The Modeling phase assesses the model based on technical statistical criteria. The Evaluation phase assesses the model''s performance against the business success criteria defined at the start of the project.'),
('203ee6ac-e5c8-4644-bb3c-855884ba8de4', 'What does "evaluate results" mean in the context of business success criteria?', '"Evaluate results" involves testing the model on real-world or test applications to see if the results make sense and truly achieve the business goals.'),
('203ee6ac-e5c8-4644-bb3c-855884ba8de4', 'What is the "review process" step in the Evaluation phase?', 'The "review process" is a more thorough review of the entire project''s execution to check if any important factor or task was overlooked. It''s a quality assurance step.'),
('203ee6ac-e5c8-4644-bb3c-855884ba8de4', 'What is the purpose of "determine next steps" in the Evaluation phase?', 'The purpose is to decide on a course of action based on the evaluation. The two main options are to proceed to deployment or to initiate a further iteration of the model development cycle.'),
('203ee6ac-e5c8-4644-bb3c-855884ba8de4', 'What are the two possible outcomes of the Evaluation phase regarding deployment?', 'The two possible outcomes are: 1) Proceed to Deployment, if the model meets the business objectives; or 2) Iterate back to an earlier phase to refine the model.'),
('203ee6ac-e5c8-4644-bb3c-855884ba8de4', 'What is the main goal of the Deployment phase?', 'The main goal is to put the model and its insights into production use within the organization''s environment.'),
('203ee6ac-e5c8-4644-bb3c-855884ba8de4', 'Why is a model not the final product of a data science project?', 'A model is not the final product because its value comes from being used. A model sitting on a laptop provides no business benefit until it is deployed, integrated into business processes, and used to make decisions.'),
('203ee6ac-e5c8-4644-bb3c-855884ba8de4', 'What does "plan deployment" involve?', '"Plan deployment" involves developing a strategy for moving the model into a production environment, including defining the deployment method, creating documentation, and setting up technical infrastructure.'),
('203ee6ac-e5c8-4644-bb3c-855884ba8de4', 'What does "plan monitoring and maintenance" entail for a deployed model?', '"Plan monitoring and maintenance" involves creating a plan to regularly check the deployed model''s performance (e.g., for data drift, accuracy degradation) and outlining a strategy for updating or retiring the model.'),
('203ee6ac-e5c8-4644-bb3c-855884ba8de4', 'What is a "final report" in the context of the Deployment phase?', 'A "final report" is a comprehensive summary of the entire project, including an executive summary, a description of the process used, the key findings, and how the results will be used.'),
('203ee6ac-e5c8-4644-bb3c-855884ba8de4', 'What is a "project review" (post-mortem) used for?', 'A "project review" is a final assessment of what went well, what could be improved, and lessons learned for future projects.'),
('203ee6ac-e5c8-4644-bb3c-855884ba8de4', 'Are the phases in CRISP-DM performed strictly sequentially? Explain.', 'No, they are not strictly sequential. The process is highly iterative. Findings in a later phase often reveal problems or new opportunities that require going back to an earlier phase to refine the data.'),
('203ee6ac-e5c8-4644-bb3c-855884ba8de4', 'Give an example of how you might loop back from the Modeling phase to the Data Preparation phase.', 'While building a model, you might discover that a feature you thought would be important is not available in its current form. You might need to loop back to the Data Preparation phase to construct a new derived feature.'),
('203ee6ac-e5c8-4644-bb3c-855884ba8de4', 'Give an example of how you might loop back from the Evaluation phase to the Business Understanding phase.', 'After evaluating the model with stakeholders, you might find that the business''s needs have shifted or that the model doesn''t solve the real business problem. This requires a loop back to Business Understanding to re-align objectives.'),
('203ee6ac-e5c8-4644-bb3c-855884ba8de4', 'What is the role of the "Data" itself throughout the entire CRISP-DM process?', '"Data" is the central element that flows through the entire process. Its understanding, preparation, and analysis are the focus of every phase.'),
('203ee6ac-e5c8-4644-bb3c-855884ba8de4', 'How does the Business Understanding phase influence the choice of modeling technique?', 'The business objective defines the type of problem to be solved (e.g., "predict churn" implies classification). This directly influences the choice of modeling technique.'),
('203ee6ac-e5c8-4644-bb3c-855884ba8de4', 'Why is it important to involve business stakeholders in the Evaluation phase?', 'It is important because they are the ultimate judges of whether the project meets the business goals. They can interpret the results in a business context.'),
('203ee6ac-e5c8-4644-bb3c-855884ba8de4', 'What is a pilot deployment, and in which phase might it occur?', 'A pilot deployment is a small-scale, limited implementation of the model to test its performance in a live but controlled environment. It might occur during the Evaluation phase or the very beginning of the Deployment phase.'),
('203ee6ac-e5c8-4644-bb3c-855884ba8de4', 'How does the CRISP-DM model help manage a data science project''s risks?', 'CRISP-DM helps manage risk by forcing a thorough understanding of the business problem and data quality before significant modeling effort is spent. Its iterative nature allows for early detection of problems.'),
('203ee6ac-e5c8-4644-bb3c-855884ba8de4', 'Compare CRISP-DM to a simple linear workflow. What are the advantages of CRISP-DM?', 'CRISP-DM''s main advantage is its iterative nature, which acknowledges that data science is an exploratory process. A linear workflow is rigid and often fails because it assumes the problem and data are perfectly understood from the start.'),
('203ee6ac-e5c8-4644-bb3c-855884ba8de4', 'If a model performs excellently on test data but fails in a live business environment, which phases of CRISP-DM were likely neglected?', 'The Business Understanding and Evaluation phases were likely neglected. The model was technically good but was not evaluated against the true business context.'),
('203ee6ac-e5c8-4644-bb3c-855884ba8de4', 'What documentation should be created during the Data Understanding phase that will be useful later?', 'A data quality report, a data description report, and an initial data exploration report should be created.'),
('203ee6ac-e5c8-4644-bb3c-855884ba8de4', 'How does the concept of "data drift" relate to the Deployment phase?', '"Data drift" refers to the change in the statistical properties of the model''s input data over time. It is a key concept in the Deployment phase''s "monitoring and maintenance" step.'),
('203ee6ac-e5c8-4644-bb3c-855884ba8de4', 'Is CRISP-DM only applicable to projects using Big Data? Explain.', 'No. CRISP-DM is a process model for data mining and works regardless of data size. The core tasks are essential whether working with a small Excel file or a massive Big Data cluster.'),
('203ee6ac-e5c8-4644-bb3c-855884ba8de4', 'Why is it important to define the data mining problem in terms of the business objective, not just a technical objective?', 'Defining the problem in terms of the business objective ensures that the entire project is focused on generating real value. A technically perfect model that doesn''t help the business is a failure.');